00:05:53.550 --> 00:05:58.901
First up, what are neurodisabilities?

00:05:58.920 --> 00:06:02.129
Besides being a really long word,
hard to pronounce sometimes.

00:06:03.779 --> 00:06:09.179
Neurodisabilities are disorders
or disabilities that affect

00:06:09.210 --> 00:06:10.210
the nervous system.

00:06:10.409 --> 00:06:14.429
That covers the brain, nerves,
and the spinal cord.

00:06:14.939 --> 00:06:18.389
It's a pretty complex system,
so you can imagine,

00:06:18.479 --> 00:06:21.989
as I mentioned, there are
a lot of different types of disabilities

00:06:21.990 --> 00:06:23.969
and disorders that this covers.

00:06:25.350 --> 00:06:28.349
All of these are important
to be considering when you're building

00:06:28.350 --> 00:06:29.591
your website.

00:06:30.509 --> 00:06:32.639
If anybody's curious
about the image on here,

00:06:32.670 --> 00:06:36.239
it might be a little bit hard
to see just because of the pastel colors,

00:06:36.240 --> 00:06:41.489
but it's not quite a watercolor,
but it's an image of a brain,

00:06:41.700 --> 00:06:44.191
including the brainstem and all of that.

00:06:49.921 --> 00:06:53.249
I just wanted to talk
about some terminology briefly

00:06:53.250 --> 00:06:55.139
before we get into things too far.

00:06:56.250 --> 00:06:59.878
The first one is neurodisability,

00:06:59.879 --> 00:07:03.977
neurological disability versus
cognitive disability.

00:07:05.609 --> 00:07:12.508
I've heard feedback that some people
aren't keen on the word neurodisability

00:07:12.509 --> 00:07:13.679
and prefer cognitive.

00:07:14.760 --> 00:07:17.698
I know that that also can happen
the opposite way.

00:07:17.699 --> 00:07:20.729
I know this happens
in a lot of different communities

00:07:20.730 --> 00:07:24.659
where there's a preferred term to use.

00:07:25.170 --> 00:07:30.778
I looked up to get more information
and found that neurodisability is more

00:07:30.779 --> 00:07:34.590
of an all-encompassing term
that includes cognitive disabilities,

00:07:35.010 --> 00:07:39.268
but cognitive refers more specifically
to processes of the brain,

00:07:39.269 --> 00:07:44.279
like memory, speech,
and problem solving.

00:07:45.000 --> 00:07:48.900
To keep things consistent
throughout this presentation,

00:07:48.959 --> 00:07:51.406
I'm going to stick to neurodisabilities

00:07:51.407 --> 00:07:55.169
because it really is all
of these different types of disabilities

00:07:55.170 --> 00:07:58.025
that can affect the things
that I'm talking about.

00:07:58.769 --> 00:08:04.980
The other terms that I wanted
to discuss is the word disability versus

00:08:05.340 --> 00:08:08.189
a difference or any other type of word.

00:08:08.220 --> 00:08:09.755
I know that there are,

00:08:10.109 --> 00:08:17.849
again, some people
who don't necessarily look at how they are

00:08:17.939 --> 00:08:21.605
in some of the terms.
For example, to take one in particular,

00:08:22.350 --> 00:08:25.140
autistic people, I know from

00:08:25.800 --> 00:08:28.408
being involved in that community
that there's a lot of people

00:08:28.409 --> 00:08:32.429
who don't like using the word disability
when talking about autism

00:08:32.640 --> 00:08:37.115
because they don't feel like
it's a disability necessarily

00:08:37.799 --> 00:08:40.324
or that it's a disorder.

00:08:41.280 --> 00:08:44.609
It's more of a difference
in the way the brain works.

00:08:45.779 --> 00:08:46.779
Again,

00:08:46.920 --> 00:08:52.529
completely want to respect that,
but also recognizing that while

00:08:52.530 --> 00:08:55.858
that is a difference,
when you're in the minority group

00:08:55.859 --> 00:08:56.859
with the difference,

00:08:57.089 --> 00:09:00.030
how you perceive
and interact with the world,

00:09:00.090 --> 00:09:02.857
you can encounter disabilities

00:09:03.389 --> 00:09:08.805
as opposed to not being part
of the bigger majority.

00:09:10.680 --> 00:09:11.908
I just want to make sure,

00:09:11.909 --> 00:09:13.738
I mean, I know we're talking
about accessibility,

00:09:13.739 --> 00:09:17.571
but I don't want
to accidentally offend anybody.

00:09:21.089 --> 00:09:26.107
Again, talked a little bit about this,
but why I care about neurodisabilities.

00:09:26.640 --> 00:09:31.439
Family history, like I said,
in my family, my son,

00:09:31.799 --> 00:09:34.925
and he gives me permission
to talk about him.

00:09:35.340 --> 00:09:39.388
He has officially been diagnosed with four
of the different types of disabilities

00:09:39.389 --> 00:09:41.159
that we're going to be discussing.

00:09:43.020 --> 00:09:45.990
Those disabilities have had
a huge impact on his life.

00:09:46.979 --> 00:09:50.819
If you were to meet him on the street,
you wouldn't look at him and go,

00:09:50.880 --> 00:09:52.860
"Oh, he has disabilities."

00:09:54.029 --> 00:09:56.578
Even if you were to hang out with him
for an afternoon,

00:09:56.579 --> 00:10:00.253
you still might not think
that he has any disabilities.

00:10:00.254 --> 00:10:01.410
I guarantee you,

00:10:01.709 --> 00:10:07.289
as his mother, I have seen he has
struggles with various different things.

00:10:07.620 --> 00:10:09.569
His disabilities are real,

00:10:10.859 --> 00:10:14.763
but there's some people
who have even said to me,

00:10:14.764 --> 00:10:17.609
"Oh, he's just a kid,
he'll grow out of that."

00:10:18.060 --> 00:10:21.008
He's not a kid anymore.
He has not grown out of it.

00:10:21.009 --> 00:10:23.134
He will not grow out of it.

00:10:23.709 --> 00:10:28.501
Again, this is just one of those things
that has really impacted my life.

00:10:30.504 --> 00:10:35.349
I just see how it affects
websites in general,

00:10:35.350 --> 00:10:36.670
as well as I'm working with them.

00:10:37.420 --> 00:10:39.759
Also, we've got the prevalence
in the tech industry.

00:10:40.899 --> 00:10:45.700
There are a lot of people
who work in our industry,

00:10:45.730 --> 00:10:50.199
whether it's by fluke
or whichever studies you want to quote,

00:10:50.590 --> 00:10:54.249
but we do have
a fairly high prevalence of things

00:10:54.250 --> 00:10:56.499
like ADHD and autism

00:10:57.910 --> 00:11:01.914
and other various neurodisabilities
in our industry.

00:11:02.948 --> 00:11:07.540
Again, it's close to home,
something that I witness

00:11:07.569 --> 00:11:10.030
every day in my colleagues and my family.

00:11:10.809 --> 00:11:16.478
Then the last thing is in my six
or so years of learning

00:11:16.479 --> 00:11:17.740
about accessibility,

00:11:17.769 --> 00:11:20.389
working on accessibility remediation,

00:11:21.609 --> 00:11:30.518
I found that it's harder
to call out some of the issues that we see

00:11:30.519 --> 00:11:33.099
on websites
because it's less quantifiable.

00:11:34.210 --> 00:11:40.330
You don't get a lot of things
coming through on automated tests,

00:11:41.200 --> 00:11:45.249
which we know don't show
all of the issues on a site,

00:11:45.759 --> 00:11:48.039
but even within the fraction
that they do show,

00:11:48.219 --> 00:11:54.099
it's not so often
the neurodisability issues that they find.

00:11:54.100 --> 00:11:58.720
It's usually various other ones
that are more easy to catch.

00:12:00.669 --> 00:12:01.689
That's, again,

00:12:01.690 --> 00:12:05.197
a little bit about me and why this
is really important to me.

00:12:09.727 --> 00:12:11.525
Neurodisabilities,

00:12:11.526 --> 00:12:16.106
I like to think of as the Linux OS
of the accessibility world.

00:12:18.670 --> 00:12:21.730
I like to think if Family Feud
did one of their top 10 surveys,

00:12:23.079 --> 00:12:27.609
probably not top 10, but it said,
we asked a hundred people,

00:12:28.120 --> 00:12:30.743
what operating system
does your computer use?

00:12:31.299 --> 00:12:34.989
You're going to see a lot of PCs
and Macs, and there'll be

00:12:34.990 --> 00:12:36.699
a nice little group of Linux there.

00:12:37.450 --> 00:12:40.300
Again, mostly tech people probably,

00:12:41.260 --> 00:12:43.809
but those top two answers
are going to be PC,

00:12:43.810 --> 00:12:45.339
Windows, and Mac.

00:12:47.319 --> 00:12:50.379
If you did a similar survey
about disabilities,

00:12:51.009 --> 00:12:55.390
you're going to see
a lot more of, if you ask people,

00:12:55.480 --> 00:12:58.478
what do we need to consider
for website accessibility?

00:12:58.479 --> 00:13:00.608
You're going to see some more answers.

00:13:00.609 --> 00:13:04.269
There'll be more than two main ones,
but the minority answer

00:13:04.810 --> 00:13:08.026
from what I found
is neurological disabilities.

00:13:15.010 --> 00:13:18.219
When I talk about that and say like,
most of the time you're going to get

00:13:18.369 --> 00:13:20.889
these other answers and not
so much the neurodisabilities,

00:13:20.919 --> 00:13:23.230
you can look and see for yourself.

00:13:23.259 --> 00:13:27.186
If you were to Google or use
whatever other search engine you wanted

00:13:27.187 --> 00:13:31.449
to use and search up online tips
or just tips for accessibility fixes

00:13:31.690 --> 00:13:32.690
for websites,

00:13:33.070 --> 00:13:36.580
your usual search results are going
to be for visual disabilities,

00:13:36.670 --> 00:13:39.250
physical disabilities,
and audio disabilities.

00:13:39.849 --> 00:13:43.479
Those things like alt text,
color contrast,

00:13:43.540 --> 00:13:44.619
font sizes,

00:13:45.100 --> 00:13:46.299
keyboard navigation,

00:13:47.229 --> 00:13:48.490
all important things,

00:13:48.850 --> 00:13:52.988
but it's a lot less likely
that you're going to see

00:13:52.989 --> 00:13:56.037
on a top 10 list something
to do with neurodisability.

00:13:58.347 --> 00:13:59.529
As I mentioned,

00:14:00.249 --> 00:14:02.470
neurological disabilities
are often overlooked

00:14:02.800 --> 00:14:04.407
and also under-considered.

00:14:05.229 --> 00:14:08.230
They're not usually accommodated
with overlay plugins.

00:14:08.500 --> 00:14:10.959
Some of them are, if you have,

00:14:11.290 --> 00:14:15.668
say, dyslexia, there's, I know,

00:14:15.669 --> 00:14:18.968
some different settings for that,
but a lot of them are not something

00:14:18.969 --> 00:14:21.249
that can be accommodated
with an overlay plugin.

00:14:22.569 --> 00:14:25.809
Then they actually affect
a larger population than you might expect,

00:14:25.840 --> 00:14:30.639
again, particularly in the tech community,
but when we talk about the fact

00:14:30.640 --> 00:14:33.669
that there are
temporary and situational disabilities

00:14:33.670 --> 00:14:35.410
too, at some point,

00:14:35.993 --> 00:14:39.308
I really find it hard
to believe that there is anybody

00:14:39.309 --> 00:14:43.149
who has never experienced
a neurological disability before.

00:14:46.330 --> 00:14:49.058
Hopefully, by the end of this talk,
you'll have a little bit more

00:14:49.059 --> 00:14:53.949
of an appreciation for how people visiting
your site every day may be using it well,

00:14:54.549 --> 00:14:56.682
or conversely struggling with it.

00:15:00.432 --> 00:15:03.681
All right, so let's talk
about some actual neurodisabilities.

00:15:03.682 --> 00:15:08.259
Again, please note, these are
by no means a complete list.

00:15:08.559 --> 00:15:11.110
These are also brief, generalized.

00:15:11.139 --> 00:15:12.670
They're not a complete description.

00:15:12.730 --> 00:15:16.749
This is more to do with focusing
on elements that are relative

00:15:16.750 --> 00:15:19.089
to interacting with websites.

00:15:20.559 --> 00:15:21.559
First up,

00:15:22.029 --> 00:15:25.420
ADHD,
attention deficit hyperactivity disorder.

00:15:26.080 --> 00:15:28.509
This impacts part of the brain
that helps us plan,

00:15:28.569 --> 00:15:31.299
focus on, and execute tasks.

00:15:31.985 --> 00:15:36.220
Somebody with ADHD may have
difficulty focusing.

00:15:36.609 --> 00:15:38.470
They might be easily distracted.

00:15:38.859 --> 00:15:41.259
Those two things
are actually not the same.

00:15:42.519 --> 00:15:46.118
They may have short-term memory issues,
and they may have difficulty

00:15:46.119 --> 00:15:47.230
making decisions.

00:15:49.030 --> 00:15:50.109
All of these things

00:15:50.620 --> 00:15:52.690
could come into play
when they're using a website.

00:15:55.899 --> 00:15:56.919
Here I've got

00:15:58.329 --> 00:15:59.979
a picture of a little boy who's

00:16:00.850 --> 00:16:02.770
a fork in the path.

00:16:03.159 --> 00:16:05.769
He could go this way or that way
trying to make a decision,

00:16:06.099 --> 00:16:11.708
trying to represent that difficulty
making decisions aspect.

00:16:13.689 --> 00:16:14.689
Next up,

00:16:15.159 --> 00:16:18.707
autism, which I've briefly touched
upon already.

00:16:18.708 --> 00:16:22.808
This is a group of conditions
that can cause social communication

00:16:22.809 --> 00:16:24.758
and behavioral challenges.

00:16:25.120 --> 00:16:29.739
Typically, autistic people
are very literal thinkers.

00:16:29.770 --> 00:16:33.245
They can be direct
and have very to-the-point communication.

00:16:34.090 --> 00:16:38.139
They can experience
sensory processing overload,

00:16:38.830 --> 00:16:42.130
and they frequently prefer
consistency, dependability,

00:16:42.190 --> 00:16:43.190
and uniformity.

00:16:43.780 --> 00:16:48.850
Just to help make the point
of the very literal thinkers,

00:16:48.910 --> 00:16:51.747
I've got this image here of--

00:16:52.738 --> 00:16:53.979
oh, I've forgotten his name.

