00:17:20.410 --> 00:17:23.173
Okay, so then we also have learning
disabilities.

00:17:23.174 --> 00:17:28.088
This is a wide variety
of information processing problems

00:17:28.089 --> 00:17:32.140
that prevent a person from learning
a new skill and using it effectively.

00:17:33.369 --> 00:17:37.232
We see learning disabilities
with reading, which is dyslexia,

00:17:37.869 --> 00:17:41.289
writing, which is dysgraphia,
processing numbers,

00:17:41.290 --> 00:17:42.290
which is dyscalculia.

00:17:42.609 --> 00:17:44.329
I'm pretty sure
there's a couple other ones,

00:17:44.500 --> 00:17:48.163
but these are just the ones
that I wanted to address tonight.

00:17:48.164 --> 00:17:50.140
Really important to note,

00:17:50.800 --> 00:17:55.329
these are not related
in any way to intelligence.

00:17:55.480 --> 00:17:59.590
Somebody having a learning disability
doesn't mean that they aren't as smart.

00:18:00.130 --> 00:18:04.748
It just means that they have
this processing problem that makes things

00:18:04.749 --> 00:18:05.749
a little bit harder.

00:18:06.280 --> 00:18:08.184
Not impossible, just harder.

00:18:09.339 --> 00:18:14.949
I hope this image of numbers and letters
isn't too crazy for it's actually starting

00:18:14.950 --> 00:18:16.330
to bother me.

00:18:18.160 --> 00:18:20.892
Then we've got memory impairments.

00:18:21.939 --> 00:18:24.729
Inability to remember information,
which can come

00:18:24.730 --> 00:18:27.908
from a variety of other disabilities
or disorders,

00:18:27.909 --> 00:18:31.449
or can just be its own issue on its own.

00:18:32.109 --> 00:18:35.499
We've short
or long-term memory impairments.

00:18:35.919 --> 00:18:40.284
We have things like dementia,
concussion, PTSD.

00:18:40.660 --> 00:18:45.400
Those are all things that will affect
memory in very specific ways,

00:18:45.700 --> 00:18:47.469
but then there's also working memory,

00:18:48.459 --> 00:18:53.589
which is what can you keep in,
so for as an example,

00:18:53.740 --> 00:18:56.830
if somebody were to say
to you, what is five plus two?

00:18:57.940 --> 00:19:00.760
You store those two numbers
in your head as you're adding them,

00:19:01.150 --> 00:19:04.869
and so somebody with working
memory may not remember those very,

00:19:04.870 --> 00:19:07.599
very short things
that they're using right now.

00:19:08.980 --> 00:19:14.166
They may not be able to carry
on other tasks that follow from that.

00:19:17.046 --> 00:19:23.466
My favorite memory loss icon
is Dory here from Finding Nemo.

00:19:26.586 --> 00:19:29.436
I believe this is the last one,

00:19:30.639 --> 00:19:32.052
mental health.

00:19:32.053 --> 00:19:34.630
This is something that I don't think
a lot of people consider

00:19:34.690 --> 00:19:37.208
when we're talking
about neurodisabilities,

00:19:37.209 --> 00:19:40.599
but it absolutely can have
an impact in a variety of ways.

00:19:41.589 --> 00:19:44.739
Mental health can affect
cognitive, emotional,

00:19:44.799 --> 00:19:46.179
and behavioral well-being.

00:19:47.349 --> 00:19:50.859
It basically affects how we think,
feel, and act.

00:19:51.610 --> 00:19:56.499
There's, again,
a variety of different disorders

00:19:56.529 --> 00:19:57.760
and disabilities here,

00:19:58.059 --> 00:20:03.066
some including paranoia, schizophrenia,
depression, and anxiety.

00:20:03.790 --> 00:20:06.128
People
with some of these mental health issues

00:20:06.129 --> 00:20:10.050
could experience difficulty focusing,
difficulty processing

00:20:10.051 --> 00:20:12.034
or understanding information.

00:20:13.179 --> 00:20:16.899
An interesting thing
that I recently learned was that,

00:20:16.989 --> 00:20:19.420
or didn't really necessarily think
of in this way,

00:20:19.960 --> 00:20:22.926
but even
if the mental health issues themselves

00:20:22.927 --> 00:20:26.008
aren't causing difficulties or struggles,

00:20:26.400 --> 00:20:32.100
the effects of their medication
that they may be taking could have

00:20:32.460 --> 00:20:33.990
side effects that impact.

00:20:34.620 --> 00:20:38.130
Some medication side effects
are blurred vision or hand tremors.

00:20:38.699 --> 00:20:44.436
Those kinds of things could also affect
websites accessibility.

00:20:50.879 --> 00:20:52.959
Oh, I was wrong.
There's one more.

00:20:53.609 --> 00:20:55.379
Seizure and vestibular disorders.

00:20:55.649 --> 00:20:58.529
This is the one
that you will probably find

00:20:58.530 --> 00:21:02.070
when you're doing
that top 10 accessibility fixes.

00:21:03.329 --> 00:21:06.148
These are disorders that can cause
seizures or other issues

00:21:06.149 --> 00:21:07.408
with the vestibular system,

00:21:07.409 --> 00:21:09.840
which is your inner ear
and brain connection.

00:21:10.349 --> 00:21:13.739
These are things like epilepsy,
migraines, nausea,

00:21:13.980 --> 00:21:16.097
and dizziness.

00:21:17.790 --> 00:21:20.608
This lots of times you might find
things about like,

00:21:20.609 --> 00:21:22.709
don't have flash and things
are like movement.

00:21:23.190 --> 00:21:28.288
That's usually related to the epilepsy,
at least it's the first thing that people

00:21:28.289 --> 00:21:31.858
tend to think of when thinking
about those kinds of things with websites,

00:21:31.859 --> 00:21:34.530
but it does affect
all kinds of different things.

00:21:34.949 --> 00:21:36.689
Like I said, with my migraines,

00:21:37.259 --> 00:21:38.909
if it's really bad,

00:21:38.969 --> 00:21:42.150
I have a really hard time
looking at websites in general.

00:21:42.929 --> 00:21:45.269
If there are different things
happening that we're going to talk

00:21:45.270 --> 00:21:46.507
about in a little bit,

00:21:47.010 --> 00:21:50.308
they can actually make my migraine worse
or make it really extra hard for me

00:21:50.309 --> 00:21:53.497
to be looking at a screen
and dealing with what's going on.

00:21:54.960 --> 00:21:59.488
So I've got this image here
of what I'm pretty sure is a path

