Hopefully you don't though,
from looking at that.

00:22:14.279 --> 00:22:18.989
Now that you've got
an understanding of what people

00:22:18.990 --> 00:22:22.327
with neurological disabilities
might be experiencing with your website,

00:22:23.220 --> 00:22:26.819
or at least how they may be dealing
with things for themselves that may impact

00:22:26.940 --> 00:22:28.649
their experience on your website,

00:22:29.279 --> 00:22:33.180
how can you ensure that you are making
your best efforts to make

00:22:33.269 --> 00:22:36.149
your website accessible
for this group of people

00:22:36.390 --> 00:22:38.969
so that it's a pleasant
and successful experience?

00:22:39.329 --> 00:22:42.960
It's also at the end of the day,
this is about you and your website.

00:22:43.289 --> 00:22:44.409
If you're trying to convert,

00:22:45.029 --> 00:22:48.219
people can't navigate your site,
you won't get those conversions.

00:22:49.380 --> 00:22:52.798
Again, this is not a comprehensive list,
but a few tips hopefully

00:22:52.799 --> 00:22:54.520
to get you started in the right direction.

00:22:57.240 --> 00:22:59.639
You may actually already be familiar
with some of these,

00:22:59.939 --> 00:23:03.145
whether it's for some
of these basic accessibility tips

00:23:03.146 --> 00:23:04.823
that you may have heard of.

00:23:04.824 --> 00:23:08.069
It could be because
of something else like SEO

00:23:08.100 --> 00:23:11.400
that sometimes comes into play
as you learn some of these things.

00:23:11.970 --> 00:23:17.700
Then even just if you're a content writer
or if you're a front-end developer,

00:23:18.059 --> 00:23:21.329
you may just have experienced
these as best practices

00:23:21.629 --> 00:23:25.889
and maybe don't even know
why they're the best practice

00:23:25.919 --> 00:23:27.535
for websites.

00:23:27.536 --> 00:23:29.758
Hopefully, this will give you
a little bit more information

00:23:29.759 --> 00:23:33.000
and a little bit more ground to stand on
if you ever have to convince somebody

00:23:33.209 --> 00:23:34.874
that this is the right way to go.

00:23:37.237 --> 00:23:40.244
We'll start with text alignment.

00:23:41.909 --> 00:23:46.619
You might instinctively do this
because it's just what we've gotten used

00:23:46.620 --> 00:23:53.716
to with web but left align is usually
the best thing to go with text.

00:23:55.020 --> 00:23:58.739
Some people just feel like it looks
more modern, more professional,

00:23:59.369 --> 00:24:03.689
but it also does have benefits
to people who are easily distracted,

00:24:04.020 --> 00:24:05.879
people who are having trouble focusing,

00:24:06.509 --> 00:24:10.649
people with reading disabilities,
lots of different people.

00:24:11.490 --> 00:24:12.989
A lot of these actually,

00:24:13.350 --> 00:24:19.079
your average Joe kind of person
would also sometimes have these issues

00:24:19.080 --> 00:24:20.759
when we go too far,

00:24:20.760 --> 00:24:25.110
too intense with some of these different
don'ts that we're going to look at.

00:24:26.040 --> 00:24:28.559
The do here is left-align text.

00:24:29.070 --> 00:24:33.209
There are two don'ts,
so don't center and don't justify.

00:24:34.319 --> 00:24:38.400
These are not-- well,
the centering I'll say is not an absolute.

00:24:38.609 --> 00:24:41.130
I don't think
on web you should ever justify though.

00:24:42.030 --> 00:24:43.030
You can see here,

00:24:43.260 --> 00:24:47.759
and I know it's a bit hard on a monitor
if we had a really big screen

00:24:47.849 --> 00:24:53.459
or bigger examples if I'm not very good
at flipping between slides

00:24:53.519 --> 00:24:57.718
and the internet in a demo,
so I can't do it that way,

00:24:57.719 --> 00:25:03.059
but trying to give you an example here
of this is what centered text looks like.

00:25:04.200 --> 00:25:09.899
The longer it is, the harder
if you can imagine reading

00:25:09.930 --> 00:25:14.610
across and after several lines,
trying at the end of one line,

00:25:14.909 --> 00:25:20.518
trying to figure out where the next line
starts when they're all jagged and there's

00:25:20.519 --> 00:25:22.529
no rhyme or reason to it.

00:25:22.860 --> 00:25:24.149
It can get really difficult.

00:25:25.230 --> 00:25:27.870
That's one of the reasons to not center.

00:25:28.800 --> 00:25:31.260
Sometimes if it's short text,
just a couple of lines,

00:25:31.289 --> 00:25:32.289
it's not too bad,

00:25:32.309 --> 00:25:36.689
but when we have long lines
like this, long paragraphs,

00:25:36.809 --> 00:25:40.770
wide paragraphs, it can be really hard
to read centered text.

00:25:41.580 --> 00:25:42.838
Justified text,

00:25:42.839 --> 00:25:47.249
and this is where you've got the text goes
all the way to the left and all the way

00:25:47.250 --> 00:25:51.899
to the right, so you end up with bigger,
different-sized gaps in between words.

00:25:52.529 --> 00:25:57.629
This is something that we're used
to seeing in books, in print,

00:25:57.960 --> 00:25:59.729
but when it comes to online,

00:26:00.029 --> 00:26:03.778
it actually, and possibly this
is an issue in print too,

00:26:03.779 --> 00:26:09.149
I guess I never really considered
print accessibility very much.

00:26:10.230 --> 00:26:14.279
What you can see here is these big gaps
that get left,

00:26:14.520 --> 00:26:17.969
they actually create patterns in the text.

00:26:18.209 --> 00:26:22.469
Somebody who is easily distracted
might lock onto those patterns

00:26:22.470 --> 00:26:24.480
and they call them white rivers.

00:26:25.320 --> 00:26:28.620
Instead of seeing the words,
all they can see is the white space

00:26:28.649 --> 00:26:30.180
in between them.

00:26:30.330 --> 00:26:33.000
If you can't see the words,
it makes it really hard to read.

00:26:37.049 --> 00:26:39.210
The next one is line length.

00:26:39.269 --> 00:26:42.359
This goes hand in hand with the alignment.

00:26:43.649 --> 00:26:46.800
Ideally, do use shorter lines.

00:26:47.460 --> 00:26:50.879
Shorter line length,
don't use longer full-width paragraphs.

00:26:50.910 --> 00:26:53.399
If you can imagine,
especially if something

00:26:53.400 --> 00:26:57.269
is full width and then you've got
a 27-inch monitor with your screen

00:26:57.719 --> 00:27:01.139
that big, trying to read
all the way across.

00:27:01.319 --> 00:27:05.100
Then, like I said on the previous slide,
trying to go from the end of this line

00:27:05.309 --> 00:27:09.359
and find the beginning of this line
when you've got all that screen to cross

00:27:09.719 --> 00:27:12.389
can be really tricky
to find where you are.

00:27:13.379 --> 00:27:16.620
It also just becomes harder to scan.

00:27:17.460 --> 00:27:21.718
We know that people
tend not to read websites in depth,

00:27:21.719 --> 00:27:22.848
they scan websites.

00:27:22.979 --> 00:27:26.999
When you've got narrower text
that is left aligned,

00:27:27.030 --> 00:27:31.290
it's a lot easier to scan and find
the information that you're looking for.

00:27:35.429 --> 00:27:38.671
Couple of do's and don'ts
for navigation here.

00:27:39.480 --> 00:27:43.320
Do make important information easy
to find.

00:27:44.129 --> 00:27:45.690
Do make your site searchable,

00:27:45.870 --> 00:27:50.671
and do group similar pages into submenus
to keep your top navigation short.

00:27:52.081 --> 00:27:54.899
Making the important information easy
to find.

00:27:55.529 --> 00:27:59.250
If you know that people
are always going to this page,

00:27:59.669 --> 00:28:01.231
whatever that may be,

00:28:01.530 --> 00:28:04.409
you may want to consider
that goes in your top nav.

00:28:04.440 --> 00:28:06.971
You want to make it really easy
for people to get the information

00:28:06.972 --> 00:28:08.002
that they're trying to find.

00:28:08.003 --> 00:28:10.828
If you know there's a page
that they're struggling to find,

00:28:10.829 --> 00:28:12.809
but that they really need
to get to, again,

00:28:12.839 --> 00:28:16.323
make that really easy
in the navigation to find.

00:28:17.460 --> 00:28:21.689
Having a search in your navigation
or in your header area

00:28:22.290 --> 00:28:24.980
helps people in a variety of ways.

00:28:25.559 --> 00:28:28.495
If I've already gone to your site
and I know I'm looking for something,

00:28:28.496 --> 00:28:33.184
but I can't remember what page it was on,
having that search can really help.

00:28:34.380 --> 00:28:39.299
Likewise, if I've never been
to your site and I know

00:28:39.300 --> 00:28:44.879
that there's probably some information
about XYZ on here that I would find useful

00:28:44.880 --> 00:28:46.106
or interesting,

00:28:46.107 --> 00:28:49.620
I don't want to have to navigate
through your whole homepage hoping to find

00:28:49.621 --> 00:28:52.078
a link and try to search
through every page.

00:28:52.079 --> 00:28:54.960
Having that search
is really, really helpful,

00:28:55.619 --> 00:28:58.679
and that will help keep people
more focused.

00:28:58.680 --> 00:29:01.993
They'll get less distracted
by all of the other things on your page.

00:29:02.385 --> 00:29:06.305
Then grouping similar pages
to keep that top navigation short.

00:29:06.540 --> 00:29:09.836
On the flip side,
don't build long top menus.

00:29:10.619 --> 00:29:14.129
They tend to overflow, especially
if they start going on to multiple lines,

00:29:14.669 --> 00:29:17.160
all of those options

00:29:18.509 --> 00:29:22.289
staring at you when you're trying
to figure out where you want

00:29:22.290 --> 00:29:25.020
to go can be really overwhelming
for some people.

00:29:25.469 --> 00:29:30.180
If you keep things short and concise
and group similar pages together,

00:29:31.170 --> 00:29:34.620
things that make sense to group
together, that will really help people

00:29:34.740 --> 00:29:35.789
navigate your site.

00:29:36.300 --> 00:29:37.679
Also really important,

00:29:37.680 --> 00:29:39.780
don't hide your contact information.

00:29:41.880 --> 00:29:45.838
If people need to contact you,
we've gotten used to certain standards

00:29:45.839 --> 00:29:49.920
and norms, so contact information
is usually like in the top right.

00:29:50.760 --> 00:29:53.950
If it's not there, usually
the next place you go look is

00:29:53.951 --> 00:29:56.549
in the footer,
but almost always like that top right,

00:29:56.580 --> 00:29:59.819
there's no real reason
to deviate from that.

00:30:00.659 --> 00:30:01.980
Keep it where people expect it.

00:30:02.700 --> 00:30:07.019
Then also don't create mismatched submenus
that don't belong under

00:30:07.020 --> 00:30:08.159
their parent menu item.

00:30:08.459 --> 00:30:09.989
People will never find them that way.

00:30:10.589 --> 00:30:13.829
Keep things short, easy
to find, searchable,

00:30:14.670 --> 00:30:16.019
and that will be really helpful.

00:30:19.409 --> 00:30:23.010
Also a couple of words
on screen readers and captioning.

00:30:23.099 --> 00:30:29.179
I know that this
does fall under either people

00:30:29.180 --> 00:30:33.560
with audio disabilities or people
with visual disabilities,

00:30:33.829 --> 00:30:36.709
but they aren't actually
the only people using screen readers,

00:30:36.949 --> 00:30:38.959
captioning, transcripts,

00:30:40.839 --> 00:30:41.839
and subtitles.

00:30:41.840 --> 00:30:45.979
There are a variety of people
who use them for different reasons.

00:30:46.880 --> 00:30:50.540
You want to make sure
that when you are putting out content,

00:30:50.960 --> 00:30:56.179
that it can be consumed in multiple ways
and that there's the ability to get

00:30:56.180 --> 00:31:01.369
the audio or the video,
I guess, the audio of any video

00:31:01.370 --> 00:31:06.139
or of text and transcripts of audio
or video so that people have access

00:31:06.140 --> 00:31:11.998
to the content if they can't or prefer
not to use your audio or video files.

00:31:13.734 --> 00:31:17.630
As I said, don't assume screen readers
and captioning are only for people

00:31:17.631 --> 00:31:19.838
with audio and visual disabilities.

00:31:20.060 --> 00:31:28.819
In addition to somebody say who has ADHD,
they might find it hard to follow along

00:31:28.820 --> 00:31:31.219
with video if they're just watching it.

00:31:32.210 --> 00:31:39.230
I know there are a lot of people with ADHD
who actually need to have multiple things

00:31:39.260 --> 00:31:42.049
going on at once, things
that they're controlling

00:31:43.100 --> 00:31:46.760
in order to concentrate
on the thing they need to concentrate on,

00:31:46.879 --> 00:31:47.959
and so having

00:31:48.680 --> 00:31:53.240
subtitles on a video is really helpful
to keep them focused.

00:31:54.260 --> 00:31:56.269
Then there are also people,

00:31:56.270 --> 00:31:58.399
if you think
about second language learners,

00:31:58.699 --> 00:32:03.320
they may be using your videos
or your audio or the transcripts

00:32:03.650 --> 00:32:07.909
to help them understand,
but also to help them learn.

00:32:08.450 --> 00:32:12.590
There's a wide variety of people
using screen readers and captioning.

00:32:14.450 --> 00:32:16.999
Another example, I mentioned
the working memory before.

00:32:17.300 --> 00:32:19.999
Subtitles on a video tutorial,
for example,

00:32:20.000 --> 00:32:21.710
can be really helpful for somebody

00:32:22.249 --> 00:32:27.523
with working memory issues to follow along
and keep on track with what you're saying

00:32:27.524 --> 00:32:28.712
and showing.

00:32:31.459 --> 00:32:34.535
Forms are always a fun one
for accessibility.

00:32:36.320 --> 00:32:40.368
I'm not going to get
into all of the different kinds of traps

00:32:40.369 --> 00:32:44.419
that you could have on forms,
but something about labels,

00:32:44.570 --> 00:32:46.340
really important to bring up.

00:32:46.850 --> 00:32:52.040
Make sure that you are using labels
and that you're not using placeholder text

00:32:52.250 --> 00:32:53.250
as labels.

00:32:53.390 --> 00:32:54.499
They are not the same.

00:32:55.160 --> 00:32:59.007
They do not behave the same
for screen readers.

00:32:59.419 --> 00:33:01.178
Also, you can see,

00:33:01.999 --> 00:33:05.330
if you see these pictures,
the first picture here is a form

00:33:05.629 --> 00:33:07.819
and it has a name input,

00:33:07.850 --> 00:33:10.280
an email input, and a comment
or message input.

00:33:10.430 --> 00:33:14.388
They're all properly labeled
with those two items above

00:33:14.389 --> 00:33:15.389
the input field.

00:33:15.680 --> 00:33:18.650
When I type my name,
Christina, into the name field,

00:33:18.679 --> 00:33:20.264
you can still see it's a name field.

00:33:20.749 --> 00:33:24.349
On the right side, we've got
the same image almost,

00:33:24.620 --> 00:33:27.169
except instead of those labels,

00:33:27.709 --> 00:33:28.879
name, email,

00:33:28.910 --> 00:33:32.750
and comment or message are put
in as placeholder text.

00:33:33.199 --> 00:33:35.960
When I start typing my name
into the name field,

00:33:37.640 --> 00:33:39.080
it doesn't say name anymore.

00:33:39.980 --> 00:33:41.600
If I don't remember

00:33:42.140 --> 00:33:43.609
what I was putting there,

00:33:44.660 --> 00:33:47.750
I can't fill
the form out properly anymore.

00:33:48.500 --> 00:33:53.479
This has happened to me so many times
when there's usually signing up

00:33:53.480 --> 00:33:57.320
for mail lists of different types

00:33:58.550 --> 00:34:00.649
when there's two input fields.

00:34:01.520 --> 00:34:07.489
I will often just automatically assume
that the order is name and email,

00:34:07.909 --> 00:34:11.090
but it's not always that way,
and so I start typing it

00:34:11.299 --> 00:34:15.290
in and then all of a sudden realize,
I don't think this is the right thing,

00:34:15.710 --> 00:34:18.499
but even backing out doesn't get me
the placeholder anymore

00:34:18.800 --> 00:34:21.487
and I'm not 100% sure what field I'm in.

00:34:21.889 --> 00:34:26.270
You want to make sure that you are using
proper labels as placeholder text.

00:34:30.589 --> 00:34:34.340
Order of elements
on your site is important.

00:34:34.519 --> 00:34:38.988
That's not just to say
how it looks, but also how it works

00:34:38.989 --> 00:34:43.159
when you are tabbing through a website
if you're using keyboard only.

00:34:45.619 --> 00:34:49.340
Similar to the contact
being somewhere where you can see it,

00:34:49.399 --> 00:34:51.409
stick to web standards and norms,

00:34:52.070 --> 00:34:54.110
ensure that your tab order is correct.

00:34:54.649 --> 00:34:59.149
Don't be over-creative and don't expect
users to understand novel designs.

00:34:59.839 --> 00:35:03.559
I know that we all want
something really cool and interesting

00:35:03.560 --> 00:35:06.289
on our sites and there's
lots of ways to do that,

00:35:07.069 --> 00:35:12.379
but you want to stick with staying
within the standards and norms

00:35:12.410 --> 00:35:15.739
that we have all gotten used to.

00:35:16.160 --> 00:35:20.359
Unless you're a really big company
that can break the mold,

00:35:20.360 --> 00:35:22.490
but for most of us,

00:35:22.969 --> 00:35:27.199
sticking to the standards and norms
are going to be what's best.

00:35:27.799 --> 00:35:29.149
I have an example here,

00:35:29.180 --> 00:35:32.179
and this is one that I come
across frequently

00:35:33.409 --> 00:35:36.770
and I still have to remind
myself how to use this.

00:35:37.310 --> 00:35:39.409
We've got here a screengrab.

00:35:39.800 --> 00:35:44.035
It's for an SMS authentication
and it's got my phone number

00:35:44.036 --> 00:35:47.940
blacked out there, Xed out.

00:35:48.444 --> 00:35:50.119
Then it's got, it says,

00:35:50.150 --> 00:35:53.680
it's got a label over an input field
that says "enter code".

00:35:53.869 --> 00:35:56.719
To the right of that input field,
it says "send code".

00:35:56.720 --> 00:36:02.030
That send code button
is a very light gray,

00:36:02.330 --> 00:36:04.309
almost the same color
as the white background.

00:36:05.029 --> 00:36:09.346
Then it's got a blue
verify button underneath it.

00:36:10.759 --> 00:36:13.850
I cannot tell you
how many times I've come to this site,

00:36:14.270 --> 00:36:19.699
typed in my login creds, got
to this page, and sat there waiting,

00:36:20.029 --> 00:36:22.969
staring at my phone,
waiting for my code to send

00:36:22.999 --> 00:36:26.359
because the first thing I see here
is "enter code".

00:36:26.870 --> 00:36:29.273
I assume it's automatically sent to me.

00:36:30.350 --> 00:36:31.519
Then eventually I remember,

00:36:31.520 --> 00:36:33.349
right, I have to hit
the send the code button.

00:36:33.949 --> 00:36:36.680
If you look at this, you don't think

00:36:37.909 --> 00:36:41.419
the button after the input field
is what I have to hit to get the info

00:36:41.420 --> 00:36:43.130
to go into the input field.

00:36:43.820 --> 00:36:47.870
Likewise, if you were tabbing,
you would hit the enter code field

00:36:47.930 --> 00:36:49.879
before you hit the send code field.

00:36:51.170 --> 00:36:56.239
This should really be set up in a way
that the send code button is above

00:36:56.240 --> 00:36:59.929
or before the input field
for entering the code.

00:37:03.589 --> 00:37:09.986
Content is another thing
that can be really tricky sometimes.

00:37:10.880 --> 00:37:12.926
Lots of times,

00:37:13.280 --> 00:37:16.429
if you're building out sites
and then you hand it over to somebody else

00:37:16.430 --> 00:37:21.326
to do content, you may have
a really accessible site

00:37:21.649 --> 00:37:26.183
and then they add all of the content
and suddenly

00:37:26.184 --> 00:37:28.642
we're experiencing some issues.

00:37:28.850 --> 00:37:31.728
You want to make sure
that when you have content,

00:37:31.729 --> 00:37:37.518
that your content is easy to understand
and any images or icons that are replacing

00:37:37.519 --> 00:37:39.080
text make sense.

00:37:39.409 --> 00:37:41.179
Ideally, have labels for them,

00:37:42.079 --> 00:37:43.190
but if you don't,

00:37:43.580 --> 00:37:46.790
they really should make
sense if they're important.

00:37:48.079 --> 00:37:51.050
You want to not use
complicated words and phrasing.

00:37:51.919 --> 00:37:55.219
If you use acronyms, make sure
the first time you use them

00:37:55.610 --> 00:37:58.791
that you spell out
what the acronym is for.

00:37:59.547 --> 00:38:00.547
Metaphors

00:38:00.949 --> 00:38:04.158
can get tricky sometimes, again,
going back to somebody

00:38:04.159 --> 00:38:08.085
who thinks very literally,
may not understand what you're getting at.

00:38:10.160 --> 00:38:12.409
Which isn't to say you can't have
fun with your content.

00:38:12.410 --> 00:38:15.138
Again, I mean, none of this
is about trying

00:38:15.139 --> 00:38:19.338
to take away creativity
but just being aware of how you may impact

00:38:19.339 --> 00:38:21.949
some people and how some people
may not understand what you're trying

00:38:21.950 --> 00:38:24.633
to say and so your message will be lost.

